            <description><![CDATA[<h2>Trimmy 0.7.0</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Highlight:</strong> Context-aware trimming with terminal detection, plus per-terminal aggressiveness (Cmd-C tracking + frontmost-app fallback).</li>
<li>Terminal detection now covers Ghostty, WezTerm, Alacritty, Hyper, and Warp Stable bundle IDs for context-aware trimming.</li>
<li>Aggressiveness now splits between general apps and terminals (defaults: Low + Normal), plus a “None” option to disable auto-trim in regular apps.</li>
<li>Settings: added Advanced tab and moved CLI installer, debug tools, and clipboard fallbacks there.</li>
<li>Menu bar icon now animates whenever a trim happens.</li>
</ul>
<p><a href="https://github.com/steipete/Trimmy/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md">View full changelog</a></p>
]]></description>
